Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Lightly grease a baking sheet. In a large bowl, cream together sour cream, butter, and sugar in a mixing bowl. Add the 1/2 egg, and beat until fluffy. Whisk together the flour and baking soda in a separate mixing bowl, and then mix into the creamed butter mixture. Stir in the nuts, orange zest, and melted HERSHEY'S KISSES . Drop the dough by large teaspoonfuls onto prepared baking sheet. Bake cookies in preheated oven for 10 to 12 minutes.